other_tests.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated measuring up to 9 mm in maximum diameter. There is mild enhancing appendiceal wall thickening with mild adjacent periappendiceal fat stranding. The appendix does not fill with oral contrast. Other notable findings include gastric bypass changes, concerning for gastro-gastric fistula, mild dilatation of the loop of small bowel in the left abdomen, small bilateral subcentimeter renal hypodensities, and mild amount of free fluid in the cul-de-sac.
other_tests.changes_over_time: There is a subcentimeter calcification in the lateral segment of the left hepatic lobe that is stable since the last evaluation.
